HES Commissioning Test Ping Click On Ping Button Please Check HES Commissioning First. I,Agree Do\'s Install Meter Box Between 3 to 6 Feet Height Use Screw Driver/T-spanner For Testing Box Screw/Fastners Use Crimping Machine to Crimp Thimble And Proper Taping Done on Thimble. Earthing Is Mandatory at Both Ends (i.e., Meter End and Pole End). Cable Anchor Should Be Used At Both Ends. Cable Height Should Be 5.6 Mtr Along With The Road And If Cable Crossing The Road The Height Should Be 5.8 Mitr. Proper Saddling Of Cable At 1.5 Mtr Gap. All Meters Should Be Installed In The Box. Earthing Must Be Checked Through Test Lamp At Both The Ends. Properly Tighten the Cable at Pole and Consumer End By Installing Angle and Tie the Cable Through Cable Tie/ Armour of the Cable. Properly Tighten the Cable at Anchor. Ensure Minimum Sagging of the Cable. Vermin Proofing should be Done at both Glands. Don\'t Don\'t Install Box Tilted. Don\'t Install Meter Below 3 Feet & Over 6 Feet. Don\'t Use Premises Grill For Cable Support. Angle Bracket Should Not Be Fixed With Nails And Should Not Be Closed. Don\'t Use Low Quality M. Storage Permissions Storage Permissions are required to capture image, store the image through your mobile camera and lets you easily access those on your phone. These permissions also enable the user to access attendance feature as Check-In and Check-Out and also help them to upload data on server when required. Location Permissions Location Permissions are required to use the Check-In and Check-Out feature while marking the attendance. These permissions also let your mobile to set the accurate location of the employees when they mark their attendance. This can ensure us to track the current location of any employee throughout the day and help you to locate them. User Personal Information Permissions User personal Information permissions are required to log into your social media accounts via your e-mail. These permissions also let any user to handle the sensitive information as their e-mail id, passwords and PIN. In case any user forget their password or needs to change their password they need to send the OTP to generate or reset the password. Camera Permissions NO QR CODE FOUND Camera permissions are required to access your mobile camera to open and capturing the image while using this application. Read Term & Condition Privacy Policy
